Assignment 10 - Polishing Up
Rabbit Hole Studios - Katherine Wu, David Lichtenberg, Olivia Novik, Owen Whitmore
Date: 12/05/2011

===========
How to Play
===========

Run: python main.py 
(python main.py > null (to speed up the game and not see the messages from SDL))
(Dependencies: rabbyt)

Instructions:
Use the arrow keys to move
Press 'c' to time travel (save and execute)
Press 'd' to boost
Press 'z' and 'x' to tilt
Press 'spacebar' to fire
Press 'n' to skip to the second level
Press 'ESC' or 'Enter' to quit out of certain scenes

Set your own controls on a game controller:
- You can do that at the first screen
- If you want, you can skip the first screen by clicking the [x] button on the window
  - This will map the joystick to the following: X-Fire, O-Time Travel, Triangle-Escape, Square-Boost, L1-Tilt Left, L2-Tilt Right, R2-Skip cut scenes

